# Salesforce Administrator Track – Day 1
## User Management, Security & Identity

## What is a Salesforce Administrator?

A Salesforce Administrator is responsible for managing and maintaining the Salesforce platform within an organization. Administrators ensure that users have the correct access, data is secure, business processes are configured properly, and the system runs efficiently.

### Responsibilities of a Salesforce Administrator
- Create and manage users
- Assign Profiles, Roles, and Permission Sets
- Manage security and data access
- Configure objects, fields, and applications
- Monitor user activity and login history
- Support business users
- Maintain data quality and system performance

---

# Difference Between User, Role, Profile, and Permission Set

## User
A User is an individual who logs in and uses Salesforce.

### Examples
- Student
- Faculty
- Placement Officer
- HOD
- Principal
- Salesforce Administrator

---

## Profile
A Profile determines what a user can do in Salesforce.

### Controls
- Object permissions
- Field permissions
- App access
- Login hours
- Login IP ranges

### Key Point
Every user must have exactly **one Profile**.

---

## Role
A Role determines what data a user can see through the role hierarchy.

### Example Hierarchy

Principal  
└── HOD  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;└── Faculty  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;└── Student

Placement Officer may exist in a parallel branch.

### Key Point
Roles control **record visibility**, not permissions.

---

## Permission Set
A Permission Set provides additional permissions to users without changing their profile.

### Example
A Faculty member may temporarily receive permission to manage attendance records.

### Key Point
A user can have multiple Permission Sets.

---

# Difference Between Role and Profile

| Feature | Profile | Role |
|----------|----------|----------|
| Controls Permissions | Yes | No |
| Controls Record Visibility | No | Yes |
| Required for Every User | Yes | No |
| Number Assigned | One | Usually One |
| Example | Can Edit Student Records | Can View Subordinate Records |

