# Identity Management Concepts

## Single Sign-On (SSO)

Single Sign-On allows users to log in once and access multiple applications without entering credentials again.

### Benefits
- Improved security
- Better user experience
- Reduced password management issues

---

## Identity Provider (IdP)

The system that authenticates the user.

### Example
Microsoft Azure AD

---

## Service Provider (SP)

The application the user wants to access.

### Example
Salesforce

---

## Identity Management

Identity Management ensures that:
- Correct users access the system
- Authentication is secure
- Authorization follows company policies

